    "description": "America Wideis a unique photographic documentation of America as it enters a new millennium -- a stunning collection of panoramic images from all fifty states by internationally acclaimed photographer Ken Duncan. Ken has traveled over 80,000 miles to many of America's most beautiful and awe-inspiring locations and has successfully captured the heart and soul of this great country.America Wideprovides a fresh look at a mighty nation at one of the most critical times in its history.Ken Duncan is a gifted writer as well as an award-winning photographer and, to him, the message is as important as the photographic image. Thoughout the book, Ken shares from his heart, to give an added spiritual dimension on a vast and spectacular visual journey. He urges the American nation to stand strongly rooted in turbulent times, for a country's strength -- like the strength of the giant Sequoia tree -- is in its roots.The indigenous people of Ken's homeland of Australia have a concept they call 'walk-awhile'. If you really want to know a place or a person, they say, you need to walk-awhile in that place, or with that person. Ken has spent over three years journeying the length and breadth of America, capturing on film the diversity of a nation blessed with natural abundant wonders.Through his stunning photographic images and inspirational text, Ken invites you to come walk-awhile with him on the adventure of a lifetime:America Wide.", 
